Rating: 4
I was immediately interested in this recipe after reading the ingredients, but nervous to attempt it after reading all of the reviews. Instead of following the advice of the other reviews, I decided to follow the recipe as close to the written way as possible. I DID NOT need 2 days to make it. It took me about 1.5 hours of active cooking/prepping time. I did make one major change. I cooked the short ribs in a Crock-Pot on low for about 8 hours on the low-10 hour setting and they turned out PERFECT! Also, I used beef stock as I could not find veal stock or Demi-Glace in my local grocery store and I used red wine vinegar. I took the short ribs out of the Crock-Pot and placed them in a warm oven after 8 hours. I removed all of the liquid from the Crock-Pot and transferred it to a sauce pan and boiled the liquid from the short ribs for about 45 mins on medium high, until it reduced to about 3 cups. It thickened up beautifully and was extremely tasty! Meanwhile, I cooked the vegetables (using about 16 baby portabella mushrooms) and made Horseradish and Garlic Mashed Potatoes (a lovely side to this dish!). I used frozen pearl onions and it was perfectly fine. When the carrots were tender, I removed all of the vegetables from the sauce pan and set aside. I boiled the liquid from the vegetables on medium-high for about 30 mins, in order to reduce the liquid. It reduced, but not as much as I would have wanted it to, so I discarded all but 1 cup of the liquid. I added 1 cup of the reduced short rib liquid and mixed it with the vegetables. Instead of discarding the short rib liquid or saving it for another use, I dipped each short rib in it to give them a wet/glazed look before platting them and I served the remaining liquid in a gravy dish. I served it with Regusci Cabernet Sauvignion (2005). This dish was such a hit! This will be my go-to beef short rib recipe!

