Rating: 4
Splendid. Time consuming, but well worth it. Braise a day before. (I didn't leave the beef in the sauce overnight, but probably would next time.) I would also prep ALL vegetables at the beginning, rather than in stages. Once you've got the cutting board and knife out, might as well do everything. Meat braised, and veggies prepped one day before, and the recipe becomes a snap on the day of dinner. Two things to watch out for: 1) if you plan on making the meal in one day, there will be tons of fat in the sauce when it's done braising. you can use a fat separator OR, as I did, throw the sauce in the freezer for 30 minutes while the veggies glaze. The fat will congeal at the top. 2) according to the recipe it takes 20+ minutes to reduce the stock when cooking the vegetables. that is wayyyy off. use less stock, or do not cover when you cook. i haven't found the perfect solution, but am surprised by how wrong the recipe gets this. served with potato and parsnip mash on the side. it is a wonderful, crowd pleasing meal that will have your guests demanding seconds.

