Spending a cool fall day surrounded by the smells of braising short ribs almost makes up for the fact that the golf season is almost over. Comfort food makes the off seasom almost bearable!!

Rating: 4
To the cook in search of veal stock, I find demi-glace concentrate in the soups and broth section of many gourmet and natural food stores (e.g., Whole Foods and Wild Oats). It comes in a small, flat, disc-like container, and is labeled demi-glace. It also comes in chicken, vegetable and seafood versions. For what it's worth, at times I've substituted half of the stock in this recipe with the chicken version because I was short on veal stock, and it tastes just as good.

Rating: 4
I'm a bit of a short rib freak and always looking for THE great recipe. This one just might be it. The extremely low-temp braise and perfectly balanced acidity of the sauce seem to be the hot ticket. I don't think I would change a thing and, in fact, I plan to adapt my braising recipes for other meats to this one.

